>>In the .ini file:
>>>\[PORTS]
>>>; COM1: is typically used by the scale.
>>>; COM2: is either the built-in modem (RS232) or the external modem (USB).
>>>; If the built-in modem is used. then set the Port=2,
>>>; if the external modem is used, then it is probably Port=5.
>>>; To be sure check the Ports section in Windows Device Manager (with the external modem connected).
>>>SerialPort=5
>>>
>>>\[MODEM]
>>>; Setup string for the modem, always enclosed in quotes.
>>>DialOutInit=AT&FS0=0&D2&C1
>>>
>>>\[MISC]
>>>; 1 to enable Smart Card Support, otherwise 0 (zero).
>>>;SmartCard=0
>>>;Timeout for connect error in seconds.
>>>;ConnectTimeOut=O
>>>
>>>; 1 to use IP, otherwise 0 (zero).
>>>UseIP=1
>>

Here is the ini file info he had sent:

[PORTS]
; COM1: is typically used by the scale.
; COM2: is either the built-in modem (RS232) or the external modem (USB).
; If the built-in modem is used. then set the Port=2,
; if the external modem is used, then it is probably Port=5.
; To be sure check the Ports section in Windows Device Manager (with the external modem connected).
SerialPort=5

[MODEM]
; Setup string for the modem, always enclosed in quotes.
DialOutInit=AT&FS0=0&D2&C1

[MISC]
; 1 to enable Smart Card Support, otherwise 0 (zero).
;SmartCard=0
;Timeout for connect error in seconds.
;ConnectTimeOut=O

; 1 to use IP, otherwise 0 (zero).
UseIP=1
